author: scheu
msg: The JAXB unmarshalling logic is changed to use the new Axiom "unwrapping" utility methods.
JAXB and the XMLStreamReader interfaces are defined by specifications.  Some vendors (IBM for example)
require that the vendor JAXB unmarshalling framework has access to the same vendor JAXB XMLStreamReader.
The use of same vendor technology makes it easier to reproduce behavior across different stack products and allows for tighter integration.
